  "prompt": "How much time does HSBC take to provide offer letter?",
  "response": "The time it takes for HSBC to provide an offer letter can vary depending on several factors, including the specific role, the urgency of the hiring process, the geographic location, and the internal processes of the department involved. Generally, it might take anywhere from a week to a few weeks after the final interview to receive an offer letter. However, there are cases where it might take longer.\n\nTo get a more accurate idea of the timeline, you could consider reaching out to the recruiter or HR contact you've been in touch with during the application process. They might be able to provide a more specific estimate based on your situation.",
